parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel without warning, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads empty even when the tank is full
or does not move from empty when the tank is full.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak can cause a fire, explosion, or other accidents, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: fuel leak from the top of the tank
or fuel leak from the fuel tank neck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause various safety issues, such as airbag malfunctions, engine stalling, and loss of control.
symptoms: and electrical issues with the radio and instrument panel cluster lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch and transmission failures can cause loss of control, accidents, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the low beam headlights can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The low beam headlights fail to illuminate
especially at night. In some cases
the high beams continue to function normally.
